"# Permanent medical equipment\nSanitary infrastructure 4. Planning Health-Care Facilities\n\n# Factors to Consider\nIn normal situations, planning the number and size of the health-care facilities for a given population is subject to the following considerations:\n& the concept of needs and demands -The quantification of medical services depends on the volume of real needs that must be satisfied. & the availability of human resources -The scarcity or surplus of health-care personnel will influence the profile of the curative services."